rdf:Description.lla:reason: Killed by boom falling on him
rdf:Description.lla:note: There is a detailed and heartfelt account of this crewman's death in the official log, including a full list of his belongings and an account of his wife receiving his wages owed. Wife's name identified as Mary Humphreys. Henry Humphrey's official number as Mate identified as: 86291.
This account is the first part of a voyage which continues on the next record, hence there are no details of discharge.
The 'Ann Jane' is actually the 'Anne Jane' of Aberystwyth.
Master's official certficate number: 34.105. The 'Anne Jane', is written as Ann Jane'.
